OL,3,CPort Talbot's blast furnaces now
OL,4,Cbelong to history but what's next?
OL,6,FAs one chapter of steelmaking in Port
OL,7,FTalbot comes to an end, a sense of
OL,8,Floss hangs over the plant, its
OL,9,Fworkforce and the Port Talbot
OL,10,Fcommunity. There is grief for the
OL,11,Fthousands of jobs being lost, a way of
OL,12,Fworking coming to an end, and a loss
OL,13,Fof identity.
OL,15,FThe blast furnaces now belong to Port
OL,16,FTalbot's past but the steel industry
OL,17,Fis no stranger to change and shifts in
OL,18,Ftechnology.
