OL,3,CPort Talbot's blast furnaces now
OL,4,Cbelong to history but what's next?
OL,6,FScrap metal will be melted in the
OL,7,Felectric arc instead of importing high-
OL,8,Fcarbon iron and coal. This will reduce
OL,9,Fthe carbon footprint of steelmaking by
OL,10,Fusing an abundant resource: UK scrap,
OL,11,Fwhich currently gets exported. The new
OL,12,Fplant should be operational by 2028
OL,13,Fbut it will need far fewer workers.
